//ARTICOLO MACCHINE FOTOGRAFICHE

The first mirrorless camera was introduced by Panasonic in 2008 and from then on the market has grown massively,
one after the other all the most famous players in the DSLR market starts to produce its vision of what a mirrorless
is and this was also the opportunity for brand like Fujifilm and Leica to create its own market of trustfully clients
and to be back strong and innovative.

Mirrorless allow you to swap and interchange lenses like in any DSLR, but since, like the name suggest, there's no mirror.
Cameras are smaller, more compacts and better looking if we compare them with the DSLR counterpart

Is a mirrorless camera better then a DSLR? Well, sometimes yes and no, like everything you have your pros and cons, portability and design
is something that afflict a lot the final price, also the lens prices and the absence of alternatives make the "first set-up" cost 
quite important. This is why this market is perfect for who is willing to pay quite a price for this small cameras where
technology and coolness make this products the perfect "machine" for any kind of photography, from street photography to the professional one

It's quite remarkable also what Sony is doing in the market, breaking apart the long-existing duopolio of Nikon and Canon in terms 
of professional photography. The introduction of amazing full frame mirrorless cameras and the good marketing campaign that the japanese
company is bringing a lot of well-known photographers to its side and, you know, the photography market is maybe one of the best
market in terms of client fidelity.

Here a list of the best cameras for this 2018, for every price and skill!


