// ARTICOLO DOMOTICA
You know what? It's time to admit that bringing awesome technologies into your house to make it as advanced as the Tony Stark Mansion
is getting easier and easier and first of all, prices are getting to an instersting reasonable level.

The smart house is here, for real, and it's mostly manageable directly from your smartphone everywhere you are. If many years ago
the concept of smart house were focus on ugly screens with silly interfaces we could now thank Google and Apple for forcing
smart house products manufacturers to adapt their sistem to already integrated protocols that makes really easy operations like
increasing your home temperature or checking what you have in the fridge or the quality of the air.

Thanks to the Google Home and Apple Home protocols you can let all this products of different brands to talk to each other setting up
customised scenarios. Think about being welcomed once you open your door with the Star Wars Darth Father theme followed by intermitting red
lights and digital frame that show the images of the empire and your army waiting for you. That's cool!

